cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with camera calibration, which is a fundamental task in computer vision. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - Augmented Reality (AR) is a graphics-related field and the paper deals with building an AR pipeline. 
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper presents a user study evaluating different visualization methods to guide the user to a target pose, which is related to human-computer interaction. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - Camera calibration is also an important task in robotics, especially for robot vision. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with generating calibration poses in real-time, which is related to multimedia processing.
